    "body": "Good find :+1:  Testing this introduces the overhead of another config however :(\r\n\r\nI have an alternative proposal: make fork versions and signing domain types explicitly non-overlapping. Although not strictly necessary, it avoids this kind of confusion in the future, and makes it easy to distinguish the data from logs/debug dumps, and eliminates the possibility of this bug.\r\n\r\nWe can set a high 1 bit in one, and not in the other, and reserve this bit for this purpose.\r\n",
